{
  "texts": [
    "The pre-processing stage uses a selection of keywords to obtain abstracts of highly relevant literature.",
    "Sentences that do not contain functional interactions and entity pairs are automatically excluded at this stage.",
    "In the relation extraction stage, the pre-trained large language models BERN2 and BioBERT are used for NER and RE.",
    "The associated entity-labelling schema reduces sentence complexity and improves model prediction accuracy.",
    "The post-processing stage refines the extracted relations by removing incorrectly recognised entities and assigns a novel confidence factor to quantify the correctness of an extracted relation."
  ]
}